claim.claim-text:
1. A method for forming a dual damascene line structure on a substrate, comprising: 
sequentially depositing an inter-metal dielectric and a first hard mask over the substrate; 
partially removing the first hard mask to have a positive trench pattern using a first photoresist pattern as a mask; 
forming a second hard mask having a substantially different etch selectivity from the first hard mask on the partially removed portion of the first hard mask; 
selectively removing the first hard mask to have a negative via hole pattern using a second photoresist pattern as a mask; 
partially removing the inter-metal dielectric to have a via hole pattern using the-first hard mask as a mask; and 
forming a trench and a via hole by removing the exposed first hard mask and selectively etching the inter-metal dielectric using the second hard mask.
